NOTE: The Exile was designed to use FOX HUD flight script, which gives it the ability to utilize 40 XS rare military space engines for torque instead of adjustors(to save mass). If you replace the flight script with another script, you will need to remove these torque engines and replace them all with adjustors.

ELEMENT PLACEMENT INSTRUCTIONS

1. Warp drive placement - aim from above at the center of the black and yellow checkers in the fore room and place the warp drive at:

(X=0.0, Y=-43.0, Z=1.0)

NOTE: For best acceleration the warp drive should be removed before combat and stored in a dump container pack. In order to get the warp drive to function again after combat you will need to use another remote(not the combat remote) and run a default flying construct autoconfig, then link the container hub to the warp drive and insert cells.


2. Shield placement - aim from below at the center of the black and yellow checkers in the fore room, then use precision move keys to move the shield to:

(X=0.0, Y=-45.0, Z=1.0)

3. Container placement - aim at the floor or ceiling of the top or bottom container bays to the rear of the bridge, and use the precision move keys to place the containers at:

(X=0.0, Y=132.0, Z=+/-24.5)

4. Engine placement - The Exile can fit alternate engine configurations. By default it has 2 XL engines and 8 L engines, but you can remove the L engines on top and bottom and fit XL engines in their place(requires removal of L containers).

Rearmost XL engines:

(X=+/-13.0, Y=-174.0, Z=0.0)

Fore XL engines(alt config):

(X=0.0, Y=148.0, Z=+/-25.0)

Top and bottom L engines(place with the squarish 'chip' facing inward toward the lumi-glass center):

(X=+/-7.5, Y=-170.0, Z=+/-20.0)
(X=0.0, Y=-170.0, Z=+/-31.5)

Wing L engines:

(X=+/-37, Y=-185.0, Z=0.0)

RECOMMENDED LOADOUT
L ammo box: 307 laser TH, 205 laser EM
Container hub:
720 laser TH, 480 laser EM
9600L spare xeron
T5 and T4 scrap
Cores for recoring kills

Press ESC to exit this text.
